Tutorial How to turn a Raspberry Pi into a Hotspot:

Step 1) Install DHCP software, running the following line command:

        sudo apt-get install isc-dhcp-server
 
Step 2) Configure the DHCP Server:
  2.1) Edit file /etc/dhcp/dhcpd.conf. Use your favorite text editor. This tutorial is going to use nano as text editor
        
        sudo nano /etc/dhcp/dhcpd.conf
       
       Find the word "authorative" then un-comment it
       
Step 3) At the same file, you must define the network that the DCHP will use it. Write the following lines:
      
       subnet 192.168.10.0 netmask 255.255.255.0 {
        range 192.168.10.10 192.168.10.20;
        option broadcast-address 192.168.10.255;
        option routers 192.168.10.1;
        default-lease-time 600;
        max-lease-time 7200;
        option domain-name "local-network";
        option domain-name-servers 8.8.8.8, 8.8.4.4;

       }

Step 4) Edit file /etc/default/isc_dhcp-server. Use your favorite text editor. This tutorial is going to use nano as text editor.
        Write the following line:
         
        INTERFACES="wlan0"
        
Step 5) You must turn down the interface wlan0. Use the command:
      
        sudo ifdown wlan0
        
Step 6) You must configure a static ip. Edit the file /etc/network/interfaces and add the following lines.
        Change the file looks like that:
        
        auto lo
        iface lo inet loopback
        iface eth0 inet dhcp
        allow-hotplug wlan0
        iface wlan0 inet static
          address 192.168.10.1
          netmask 255.255.255.0
          
Step 7) Configure the HostAPD
  Step 7.1) To configure it, edit the file /etc/hostapd/hostapd.conf
              
          sudo nano /etc/hostapd/hostapd.conf
          
  Step 7.2) Copy the following lines to file /etc/hostapd/hostapd.conf
        interface=wlan0
        driver=nl80211
        ssid=sense
        country_code=US
        hw_mode=g
        channel=6
        macaddr_acl=0
        auth_algs=1
        ignore_broadcast_ssid=0
        wpa=2
        wpa_passphrase=S3ns1nG_bu5
        wpa_key_mgmt=WPA-PSK
        wpa_pairwise=CCMP
        wpa_group_rekey=86400
        ieee80211n=1
        wme_enabled=1

Step 8) Open the file /etc/sysctl.conf
        Add in the file's last line:
        
        net.ipv4.ip_forward=1
        
Step 9) Running this line in the terminal:

        sudo sh -c "echo 1 > /proc/sys/net/ipv4/ip_forward"
        
Step 10) Up the interface:
    
        sudo ifup wlan0
        
Step 11) Copy the following commands at terminal:

        
        sudo iptables -t nat -A POSTROUTING -o eth0 -j MASQUERADE
        sudo iptables -A FORWARD -i eth0 -o wlan0 -m state --state RELATED,ESTABLISHED -j ACCEPT
        sudo iptables -A FORWARD -i wlan0 -o eth0 -j ACCEPT
        
Step 12) Starting the WiFi Router:
    
        sudo service isc-dhcp-server start
        
        sudo service hostapd start

Step 13) Reboot Raspberry Pi:

         sudo reboot


























